*btop*

Red letters show keys to press for functionality.  Example:  e toggles tree
view in the processes.

o   Set options
m   Main menu
p   Toggle configured preset  
        0 cpu top, left mem & net, right proc
        1 proc top, cpu bottom
        2 cpu, mem, net
        3 cpu, net
q   Quit

Panels
    1   CPU
    2   Memory  (use d to toggle disks box)
    3   Network
    4   Process
            f   Filter (e.g., PID, command, etc.
            c   Sort processes per core
            r   Reverse list
            e   Tree view
            Left, right arrows:  choose sorting method:
                name, command, threads, user, memory,
                cpu direct, cpu lazy, pid
            t   Terminate a process
            k   Kill a process
            s   Send a signal to a process

https://docs.vultr.com/how-to-install-and-use-btop-on-ubuntu-20-04
